            "separator": true,
            "spacing": "medium",
            "items": [
              { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "**AI Policy & Regulation**", "weight": "bolder", "size": "medium", "wrap": true, "color": "accent" }
            ]
          },
          { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "- Trump bans Anthropic from all federal use (Feb 27), designating it a \"supply-chain risk to national security\"; 6-month agency phase-out; $60B VC investment at risk; legal challenge planned", "wrap": true, "spacing": "small", "size": "small" },
          { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "- OpenAI swoops in with Pentagon deal hours after Anthropic ban; CEO Altman admits on March 1 deal was \"definitely rushed\" and \"optics don't look good\" — despite having publicly agreed with Anthropic's ethical redlines", "wrap": true, "spacing": "small", "size": "small" },
          { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "- Brown University study: AI chatbots acting as therapists routinely breach confidentiality and professional boundaries; EU and multiple US states weighing regulations", "wrap": true, "spacing": "small", "size": "small" },
          {
            "type": "Container",
            "separator": true,
            "spacing": "medium",
            "items": [
              { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "**Claude / Anthropic**", "weight": "bolder", "size": "medium", "wrap": true, "color": "accent" }
            ]
          },
          { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "- Anthropic refused $200M DoD contract unless Pentagon agreed to ban Claude from mass surveillance and autonomous weapons — citing unreliability of current frontier models for lethal autonomous decisions", "wrap": true, "spacing": "small", "size": "small" },
          { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "- Claude Opus 4.6 (Feb 5): 1M-token context, record coding/agentic benchmarks, detected 500+ zero-days in open-source libraries; Sonnet 4.6 (Feb 17): new default, preferred in 70% of Claude Code tests", "wrap": true, "spacing": "small", "size": "small" },
          { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "- Anthropic raises $30B at $380B valuation; $14B annual revenue disclosed alongside the round", "wrap": true, "spacing": "small", "size": "small" },
          {
            "type": "Container",
            "separator": true,
            "spacing": "medium",
            "items": [
              { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "**OpenAI / ChatGPT**", "weight": "bolder", "size": "medium", "wrap": true, "color": "accent" }
            ]
          },
          { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "- GPT-5.3-Codex (Feb 5): first model that \"helped create itself\"; dedicated to agentic coding workflows; agentic platform scale-up underway", "wrap": true, "spacing": "small", "size": "small" },
          { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "- OpenAI closes $110B funding round at $840B valuation: Amazon $50B, SoftBank $30B, Nvidia $30B; largest single-company funding round in history", "wrap": true, "spacing": "small", "size": "small" },
          {
            "type": "Container",
            "separator": true,
            "spacing": "medium",
            "items": [
              { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "**Google / Gemini**", "weight": "bolder", "size": "medium", "wrap": true, "color": "accent" }
            ]
          },
          { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "- Gemini 3.1 Pro (Feb 19): 77.1% on ARC-AGI-2 with three-tier thinking architecture, doubled reasoning vs. Gemini 3 Pro at same pricing", "wrap": true, "spacing": "small", "size": "small" },
          { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "- Samsung plans to double Gemini AI-equipped devices to 800M units by end of 2026 — pre-announcement ahead of MWC 2026 (March 3–6, Barcelona)", "wrap": true, "spacing": "small", "size": "small" },
          {
            "type": "Container",
            "separator": true,
            "spacing": "medium",
            "items": [
              { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "**AI Industry**", "weight": "bolder", "size": "medium", "wrap": true, "color": "accent" }
            ]
          },
          { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "- Big Tech pledges ~$700B in 2026 data center capex: Amazon ~$200B, Alphabet ~$185B, Microsoft ~$145B, Meta $115–135B; Nvidia GPU supply is primary bottleneck", "wrap": true, "spacing": "small", "size": "small" },
          { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "- Oracle plans 20,000–30,000 layoffs to generate $8–10B for AI infrastructure; Block (Square/CashApp) cut 4,000 employees (40%) in Feb citing cheaper AI tools replacing roles", "wrap": true, "spacing": "small", "size": "small" },
          { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "- Apple targets March 2026 for fully AI-powered Siri on iOS 26.4; running Google Gemini (1.2T params) on Apple Private Cloud Compute", "wrap": true, "spacing": "small", "size": "small" },
          { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "- MWC 2026 preview (March 3–6): AI glasses from Samsung, Alibaba/Qwen, MediaTek, iFlytek (40g, real-time translation); Samsung+AMD validate AI-RAN multi-cell deployments", "wrap": true, "spacing": "small", "size": "small" },
          {
            "type": "Container",
            "separator": true,
            "spacing": "medium",
            "items": [
              { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "**AI Startups & Funding**", "weight": "bolder", "size": "medium", "wrap": true, "color": "accent" }
            ]
          },
          { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "- Perplexity Computer (Feb 25): \"digital worker\" orchestrating 19 AI models as sub-agents — signals industry shift from single dominant model to multi-model coordination architectures", "wrap": true, "spacing": "small", "size": "small" },
          {
            "type": "Container",
            "separator": true,
            "spacing": "medium",
            "items": [
              { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "**Open Source AI**", "weight": "bolder", "size": "medium", "wrap": true, "color": "accent" }
            ]
          },
          { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "- DeepSeek V4 expected March 3: multimodal model optimized for Chinese chips (Huawei Ascend, Cambricon) — direct response to US export controls blocking Nvidia H100/H200", "wrap": true, "spacing": "small", "size": "small" },
          { "type": "TextBlock", "text": "- Chinese lab wave in February: Alibaba Qwen 3.5, MiniMax M2.5, ByteDance Seed 2.0, Zhipu GLM-5 all shipped; seven frontier models released globally in 28 days", "wrap": true, "spacing": "small", "size": "small" },
